    <div class="AssessmentProblem.identifier">102778</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.type">ShortAnswerResponse</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.statement"><p>In a river in Africa, hippos and alligators live together. There are 2 hippos for every 7 alligators in the river. If there are 72 animals all together, how many hippos and alligators are there? Explain your reasoning.</p>
</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.solution"><p>16 hippos and 56 alligators. Possible strategy: We can represent 2 hippos for every 7 alligators with a tape diagram:</p>

<p><img class="h-max-height--4-lines" src="/image_files/30696.png" /></p>

<p>There are 9 parts total and 72 animals, so that means each part represents 8 animals. There are 16 hippos, since <span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="36319">\(2 \boldcdot 8 = 16\)</span>, and 56 alligators, since <span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="44331">\(7 \boldcdot 8 = 56\)</span>.</p>
</div>
